
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `bc` yek mohasebe-gar (calculator) riyazi dar terminal ast. Ba `bc` shoma mitoonid amaliyat riyazi pishrafte ra anjam dahid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `bc -l` --> ➗ Estefade az ketabkhane riyazi standard (math library) baraye mohasebat دقیق tar mesl sin, cos, va geyre.
    🔹 `bc -q` --> 🤫 Az namayeshe payam aghazeh (startup message) jologiri mikonad.
    🔹 `bc -v` --> ℹ️ Neshan dadane version `bc`.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ bc
    bc 1.07.1
    Copyright 1991-1994, 1997, 1998, 2000, 2004, 2006 Free Software Foundation, Inc.
    This is free software with ABSOLUTELY NO WARRANTY.
    For details type `warranty'.
    1+1
    2
    quit

    🔹 Run kardan `bc` be soorate interactive va jam zadan do adad.

    $ echo "scale=2; 10/3" | bc -l

    🔹 Mohasebeye taqseem ba deghat do ragham ashar ba estefade az pipe.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ bc -l <<< "sqrt(2)"

    🔹 Mohasebeye جذر 2 ba estefade az ketabkhane riyazi va here string.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `bc` command is a command-line calculator. You can use `bc` to perform advanced mathematical operations in the terminal.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `bc -l` --> ➗ Use the standard math library for more precise calculations, such as sin, cos, etc.
    🔹 `bc -q` --> 🤫 Suppress the startup banner message.
    🔹 `bc -v` --> ℹ️ Display the version of `bc`.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ bc
    bc 1.07.1
    Copyright 1991-1994, 1997, 1998, 2000, 2004, 2006 Free Software Foundation, Inc.
    This is free software with ABSOLUTELY NO WARRANTY.
    For details type `warranty'.
    1+1
    2
    quit

    🔹 Run `bc` in interactive mode and add two numbers.

    $ echo "scale=2; 10/3" | bc -l

    🔹 Calculate division with two decimal places using a pipe.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ bc -l <<< "sqrt(2)"

    🔹 Calculate the square root of 2 using the math library and a here string.
